description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a highly motivated staff nurse to work in our new 17 bedded unit at Haltwhistle.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We currently care for patients requiring rehabilitation, step down/up care, palliative/end of life care. We also do a little ambulatory care as well as having a small minor injuries unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are mainly nurse led, with medical cover each day and a Consultant visit once weekly. We encourage staff to complete training in advanced skills to enable them to assess and treat inpatients, to carry out symptom management&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates please note that full or part time will be considered for this post. This post may also include some internal rotation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1st Level live NMC registered Nurse&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Registered Mentor. Mentorship qualification or relevant qualification (essential&lt;br /&gt;requirement for post, expectation this will be completed within an 18 month period)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Valerie Reynolds&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ward Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;valerie.reynolds@northumbria-healthcare.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01434 362200&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 18th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
